The Gamified Box (v5.0 Master Build)A sensory-first, "No UI" physical artifact designed for habit reflection and journaling. This digital basin behaves like a real object held in your hands, prioritizing tactile interaction, procedural acoustics, and physical evolution over traditional menus.🏁 The Philosophy: "No UI"This artifact is built on a "Wordless Interface" mandate. Apart from centered dialogue prompts during reflection, the interface is purely physical.Physical Logging: Tapping a glass vessel in the basin "logs" a habit, causing it to fill with color and light.Inset Navigation: Mode switching is handled by a row of small glass marbles embedded in the front frame. They ignite only when progress thresholds are met.Tactile Feedback: Every collision is felt through high-resolution haptics and heard through mathematically synthesized acoustics.💎 The 5 PillarsThe basin contains five "hollow" glass vessels that represent the core foundations of well-being:Sleep (Gold)Sunlight (Blue)Movement (Red)Nutrition (Purple)Relationships (Green)🎮 Gamified States (Unlocked via Progress)As you log habits (10% fill per interaction), the artifact evolves through several physical states:Sandbox (Default): Use the gyroscope to roll marbles or "flick" them using the screen.Orbit: A meditative state where marbles float in a circular rotation based on fill levels.Billiards: The floor transforms into green felt, racking the marbles for a physical mini-game.Pinball: Gravity shifts, brass bumpers materialize, and tapping the screen sides triggers flippers.Maze: Wooden walls materialize inside the basin, creating a labyrinth navigated by tilting.Koi Pond (Endgame): Triggered by a physical tap on the white glowing inset once all pillars reach 90%. The vessels transform into organic 3D geometries (Torus Knots, Shells, Unions) and dock into a physical wooden tray.🔊 Sensory TechnologyBen Bear Acoustic Profile: Uses the Web Audio API to synthesize "wooden/glass thumps" procedurally. Pitch and volume scale dynamically based on the force of physical impact.Dynamic Haptics: Uses navigator.vibrate to give digital objects physical weight.The Ripple: A cascading 5-note arpeggio and unique vibration pattern used for major state transitions.🛠 Technical ImplementationStandalone Engine: Built as a single, self-contained .html file.Graphics: Three.js (WebGL) with an Orthographic perspective.Physics: Matter.js 2D engine mapped to 3D space.Persistence: Hybrid support for Cloud Sync (Firestore) and Offline Save (localStorage).Mobile Optimized: Includes iOS/Android permission handling for Motion Sensors and Audio contexts.🚀 Deployment (GitHub Pages)Upload index.html to a GitHub Repository.Go to Settings > Pages.Set Source to Deploy from branch and select Main.Wait 60 seconds and open the generated link on your mobile device.Created by IthacaBen Design
